{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"profile":1,"meta":2},null,{"title":3},""],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"lang":1},""],"uses":{"params":["lang"]}},{"type":"data","data":[{"isMobile":1,"globalMapSettings":2,"mapConsent":1,"playerFaction":5,"isAdmin":1,"mapData":6,"mapUrl":11,"meta":39},false,{"grid":1,"noise":3,"markerLabel":3,"style":4},true,"color",null,{"id":7,"title":8,"description":9,"keywords":10,"url":11,"grid":12,"code_name":11},1,"Gray Zone Warfare Interactive Map | Lamang | GZW Tac Map","Explore the detailed interactive map of Lamang and delve into its rich history. Find any locations including landing zones, tasks, keys, loot spots, and more.","gray zone warfare map, gray zone warfare locations, gray zone warfare tasks, gray zone warfare missions, gray zone warfare strategy, gray zone warfare guide, gray zone warfare tips, gray zone warfare walkthrough, gray zone warfare gameplay, gray zone warfare resources, gray zone warfare objectives, gray zone warfare factions, Gray Zone Warfare Interactive Map, Gray Zone Map, GZW Map, Gray Zone Locked Doors, Gray Zone Loot Heatmaps, Gray Zone Spawns, Gray Zone Extracts, Gray Zone Warfare Enemy Spawn Maps","lamang",{"corner":13,"tileZoom":14,"mapZoom":17,"cells":20,"extent":22,"cellLabel":1,"sideLabel":3,"label":26,"steps":32},"bottom-left",{"minZoom":15,"maxZoom":16},11,19,{"minZoom":18,"maxZoom":19},14,21,{"x":18,"y":21},8,[23,23,24,25],0,14000,8000,{"type":27,"position":29},{"x":28,"y":28},"number",{"x":30,"y":31},"top","right",[33],{"zoom":34,"opacity":35,"cells":36},16.5,0.01,{"x":37,"y":38},140,80,{"title":8,"description":9,"url":40,"canonicalPathname":41,"image":42},"https://gzwtacmap.com/maps/lamang","/maps/lamang","https://gzwtacmap.com/assets/images/og/og-lamang.png"],"uses":{"params":["mapUrl"]}},{"type":"data","data":[{"test":1},"bla"],"uses":{}},null,{"type":"data","data":[{"sidebarData":1,"pageLocal":290},{"general":2,"containers":90},{"Other":3,"poi":71},[4,12,18,26,34,39,45,51,56,62,66],{"id":5,"name":6,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":8,"category":9,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},48,"Coded Doors",null,[],"general",true,false,{"id":13,"name":14,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":16,"category":9,"description":17,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},38,"COP","object",[],"\u003Cp>Combat Outposts (COPs) in Gray Zone Warfare are strategic locations that function as forward operating bases across the map. They allow players to respawn, restock supplies, interact with vendors, and turn in task items without returning to a main base. Control of these outposts significantly improves movement efficiency and overall map control.\u003C/p>\r\n\r\n\u003Cp>Certain large outposts, classified as Level 3, provide additional value. Each week, two of these major Combat Outposts gain temporary access to the Vulture vendor, offering exclusive items recovered from other players.\u003C/p>",{"id":19,"name":20,"type":21,"zoom":7,"aliases":22,"category":9,"description":25,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},22,"Easter Eggs","place",[23,24],"Easter","Egg","Special in-game locations that serve as easter eggs honoring streamers, content creators, and active members of the Gray Zone Warfare community.",{"id":27,"name":28,"type":29,"zoom":7,"aliases":30,"category":9,"description":33,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},40,"Intel","item",[31,32],"Code","Password","Folders, notes, or documents containing valuable information and codes used to unlock locks, safes, or devices with digital keypads.",{"id":35,"name":36,"type":21,"zoom":7,"aliases":37,"category":9,"description":38,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},19,"Interaction Object",[],"Objects and items in locations that have no specific purpose but can be interacted with.",{"id":40,"name":41,"type":29,"zoom":7,"aliases":42,"category":9,"description":44,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},18,"Key Spawn",[43],"static","Static locations where door keys can spawn. Each key has one or several fixed spawn points and appears randomly at one of at few of them. Keys are divided into 2 types: non-task-related and task-related.",{"id":46,"name":47,"type":21,"zoom":7,"aliases":48,"category":9,"description":50,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":10,"is_active":10},1,"Landing Zone",[49],"LZ","Special fixed locations around Lamang Island where you can infil to visit nearest place or exfil after successful raid. You have to explore the island to find new. Distance to discover new LZ is \u003Cmark>100 meters\u003C/mark>.",{"id":52,"name":53,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":54,"category":9,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},3,"Locked Doors",[55],"keys",{"id":57,"name":58,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":59,"category":9,"description":61,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},2,"Operation Base",[60],"OB","The main location that each of the 3 factions has. There you spawn, interact with vendors, or infil on new quests.",{"id":63,"name":64,"type":21,"zoom":7,"aliases":65,"category":9,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},5,"Place of Interest",[],{"id":67,"name":68,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":69,"category":9,"description":70,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},70,"Range & Rifle",[],"These are magazines that can be found throughout the Lamang island. Each magazine unlocks a specific camo variant for a particular weapon. Once you find one, you will receive a task to deliver it to the appropriate vendor. After that, you will be able to freely purchase that weapon in the corresponding camo from vendor.",[72,81],{"id":73,"name":74,"type":21,"zoom":75,"aliases":78,"category":9,"description":79,"is_published":10,"sub_category":80,"is_active_by_default":10,"is_active":10},37,"Primary POI",[76,77],0,16,[],"\u003Cp>The main locations of the island. They are divided into \u003Cspan class=\"mark\">Tier 1\u003C/span>, \u003Cspan class=\"mark\">Tier 2\u003C/span>, and \u003Cspan class=\"mark\">Tier 3\u003C/span> according to the level of AI, value and quality of loot.\u003C/p>\r\n\r\n\u003Cp>While this tier system provides a general indication of difficulty and loot quality, it's worth noting that high-tier crates can occasionally be found in Tier 2 zones.\u003C/p>","poi",{"id":82,"name":83,"type":21,"zoom":84,"aliases":87,"category":9,"description":89,"is_published":10,"sub_category":80,"is_active_by_default":10,"is_active":10},4,"Sub POI",[85,86],15.3,30,[88],"name","Small points of interest linked to main POIs. They often provide additional loot, hide something interesting or are parts of tasks.",{"Other":91,"ammo":97,"gear":108,"medicals":143,"miscellaneous":168,"mixed":199,"provisions":231,"weapon":258},[92],{"id":93,"name":94,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":95,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":7,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},71,"ATM",[],"containers",[98,104],{"id":99,"name":100,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":101,"category":96,"description":102,"is_published":10,"sub_category":103,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},20,"Ammo Box",[],"Small crates filled with various types of ammunition. Useful for quickly restocking ammo during exploration.","ammo",{"id":105,"name":106,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":107,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":103,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},65,"Mortar Ammo Box",[],[109,114,120,124,128,132,139],{"id":110,"name":111,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":112,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},57,"Equipment Box",[],"gear",{"id":115,"name":116,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":117,"category":96,"description":119,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},25,"Military Gear Crate",[118],"Supply Box","Military black crates with valuable gear inside.  The most valuable boxes with gear which you can find around Lamang Island. Inside them is a chance to find such things as a \u003Cmark>Delta\u003C/mark> backpack, a \u003Cmark>Skull Mask\u003C/mark>, \u003Cmark>M2 Vest\u003C/mark>, etc.",{"id":121,"name":122,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":123,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},60,"PMC Gear Box",[],{"id":125,"name":126,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":127,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},63,"UN Convoy Equipment Box",[],{"id":129,"name":130,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":131,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},51,"UN Equipment Box",[],{"id":86,"name":133,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":134,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},"UN Gear Crate",[135,136,137,138],"Icebox","Chiller","Cooling Box","UNRLA",{"id":140,"name":141,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":142,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":113,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},58,"Wooden Equipment Box",[],[144,154,160,164],{"id":145,"name":146,"type":15,"zoom":147,"aliases":149,"category":96,"description":152,"is_published":10,"sub_category":153,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},27,"First Aid Cabinet",[148,86],17,[150,151],"Medical","Health Pack","A wall-mounted cabinet containing basic medical supplies.  Very common, and rarely contain any valuable supplies.","medicals",{"id":155,"name":156,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":157,"category":96,"description":159,"is_published":10,"sub_category":153,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},28,"Medical Bag",[158,151],"Medic Bag","Medical containers with more unique or rare items than in First Aid Cabinets.",{"id":161,"name":162,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":163,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":153,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},69,"Medical Case",[],{"id":165,"name":166,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":167,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":153,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},41,"Military Medical Crate",[],[169,177,181,185,189,195],{"id":170,"name":171,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":172,"category":96,"description":175,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},9,"Cash Register",[173,174],"Money","Cashbox","\u003Cp>Cash registers are lootable containers where you can find a certain amount of money. They are divided into two tiers: white (tier 1) and black (tier 2).\u003C/p>\r\n\u003Cp>They can be found in kiosks, shops, and various commercial locations that handle money.\u003C/p>","miscellaneous",{"id":178,"name":179,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":180,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},50,"Jewelry Box",[],{"id":182,"name":183,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":184,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},53,"Metal Box",[],{"id":186,"name":187,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":188,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},46,"Purse",[],{"id":190,"name":191,"type":15,"zoom":7,"aliases":192,"category":96,"description":194,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},8,"Safe",[193],"Vault","Safes that may contain valuable items or currency. Some require a key or code to open, while others can be accessed without any tools.",{"id":196,"name":197,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":198,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":176,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},68,"Tool Box",[],[200,205,210,214,218,223,227],{"id":201,"name":202,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":203,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},44,"Briefcase",[],"mixed",{"id":206,"name":207,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":208,"category":96,"description":209,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},45,"Buried Cache",[],"\u003Cp>Buried Caches in Gray Zone Warfare are hidden loot stashes scattered across Lamang Island.\r\nThis interactive map shows all known buried cache locations, grouped by tier.\u003C/p>\r\n\u003Cp>Each cache tier differs in size and the quality of loot, ranging from rare gear and valuable items\r\nto more common supplies useful during exploration.\u003C/p>",{"id":211,"name":212,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":213,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},67,"Car Trunk",[],{"id":215,"name":216,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":217,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},42,"Civilian Chest",[],{"id":219,"name":220,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":221,"category":96,"description":222,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},43,"Duffle Bag",[],"Duffle Bags are general-purpose loot containers found across the Lamang Island. They exist in three different tiers, and can hold a wide variety of items. Their content is highly versatile, making them an unpredictable but valuable target during exploration.",{"id":224,"name":225,"type":7,"zoom":7,"aliases":226,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},66,"Jacket",[],{"id":228,"name":229,"type":29,"zoom":7,"aliases":230,"category":96,"description":7,"is_published":10,"sub_category":204,"is_active_by_default":11,"is_active":11},55,"Plastic Co